{
  "texts": [
    "Recall that diagnoses govern therapy, postoperative prognostication, and management of cancer patients (Smeltzer et al. 2021), so properly performing ML-ML-diagnostic tools impacts the in-follow routines.",
    "Early detection greatly affects survival rates and \"avoidable deaths\" (Wardle et al. 2015).",
    "It is supplied with two constituents: (i) screening and (ii) early diagnosis, or downstaging.",
    "Due to the dismal prognosis of GYN malignancies, screening (36%) is pivotal with forecast demand outweighing that of diagnosis.",
    "But while regular HPV-DNA testing, cervical cytopathology, direct visual inspection, and colposcopy, could preclude cervical cancer, screening for endometrial and ovarian cancers remains controversial."
  ]
}